==Polish==

===Etymology===
Considered derogatory until the 19th century; now the standard, neutral word. Origin uncertain; probably either from {{cog|zlw-opl|kob|gloss=pigpen}} or {{m|zlw-opl|koba|gloss=mare}}; the suffix {{m|pl||-ieta}} is found in some contemporaneous female names ({{m|pl|Markieta}}, {{m|pl|Elżbieta}}, {{m|pl|Greta}}). Displaced {{m|pl|niewiasta}} (now considered poetic) and {{m|pl|żona}} (meaning narrowed down to "wife").

